                <note rend="inline" type="source">367N.1115/219: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steger</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-16T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 16, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 86, May 10, noon. Department has replied to telegram no. 455, May 10, 4 p.m.
                    from Minister, Cairo, on subject of evacuation of Americans and has requested
                    Minister to inform you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
